OK New York: From Penn Station to Empire Complex World Speed Survey 2019 Railway Gazette China 2019 Digital Archive 2012-10-24T04:00:00+01:00 KAZAKHSTAN: The first class of KTZ staff to receive bespoke training from academics at the University of California Berkeley received their certificates on September 10. 
A team of academics from the Haas Business School is providing multi-disciplinary classes to 143 members from KTZ's headquarters and regional offices. 
The first sessions were held on September 4 in KTZ's newly-opened Centre for Transportation Technologies in Astana, which has been established to facilitate the training of KTZ staff in 'the best examples of modern railway engineering and technology'. 
2012-05-08T04:00:00 KAZAKHSTAN: State railway Kazakhstan Temir Zholy has announced plans to offer additional training to 10000 employees over the next eight years. 
The focus will be on effective management skills, key to bringing extensive modernisation of the country’s railways to completion. 
INTERNATIONAL: UK-based networking and educational association Young Rail Professionals has launched Young Rail Tours in partnership with the Young Members sections of the Institution of Mechanical Engineers’ Railway Division, the Institution of Railway Signal Engineers and the Institution of Engineering Technology Railway Technical Professional Network. 
